  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d01fd2d64a9249049aaa77d5c12a82fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: page 9
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  questionText: " What is a dissecting microscope?  \r\n"
  referenceImage: {fileID: 0}
  explanationText: A dissecting microscope is essentially a simple microscope that
    uses a single convex lens with a short focal length to magnify objects through
    angular magnification, producing an erect virtual image of the object near the
    lens.
  options:
  - ' It is a complex assembly of lenses that enables highly magnified images of
    microscopic living organisms and detailed cells and tissues. '
  - 'It is a microscope that uses a beam of accelerated electrons as its source of
    illumination.   '
  - It is an optical microscope that utilizes fluorescence and phosphorescence
  - 'It is a magnifying instrument that uses only one lens to magnify objects.  '
  correctOptionIndex: 3
